4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing law, the governing body of a
6 county or municipality may assess fees, charges, and
7 rates for the provision of solid waste services, and
8 the governing body may recover outstanding solid waste
9 utility fees, charges, and rates in a civil action,
10 suspend solid waste services, or both.
11 This bill would establish that the remedies
12 available to the governing body of a county or
13 municipality provided in the statute are the exclusive
14 remedies for nonpayment of solid waste fees, charges,
15 or rates.
16 Under existing law, a person who has not been
17 issued a certificate of exception and uses the solid
18 waste system of a county or municipality, and fails to
19 pay the solid waste fee, charge, or rate is guilty of a
20 misdemeanor.
21 This bill would remove the misdemeanor penalty.
22 This bill would also make nonsubstantive,
23 technical revisions to update the existing code
24 language to current style.
